      • listNames

        public static java.util.List<java.lang.String> listNames()
                                                  throws java.io.IOException
        Returns a List of filenames of all TileSets within the tilesets folder. The names returned will not have the .csv extension.
        Returns:
        a List of Strings containing the filenames of tilesets in the tileset directory. These names do not contain the .csv extension.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • load

        public static TileSet load(java.lang.String name)
                    throws java.io.IOException,
                           java.text.ParseException
        Loads a TileSet from disk, parses it and returns a TileSet object. The name of the returned TileSet object will not contain the .csv extension.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the tileset to load, excluding any ".csv" extension.
        Returns:
        a TileSet object loaded from disk.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
        java.text.ParseException

      • save

        public static void save(TileSet tileSet,
        java.lang.String path)
                 throws java.io.IOException
        Writes the TileSet to the specified location on disk. If a file already exists at the specified location, it will be overwritten.
        Parameters:
        path - the path on disk to write to.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an I/O error occurs.
